    "body": "See related discussion in https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/38635#issuecomment-4180523072\r\n\r\nOn non-CDMM Grace-Blackwell machines, each GPU's HBM is exposed as a separate NUMA node with memory but no CPUs (e.g., nodes 2, 10, 18, 26). `nvmlDeviceGetNumaNodeId()` returns these memory-only nodes, causing `numactl --cpunodebind` to fail with \"Invalid argument\".\r\n\r\nFix by checking whether the NVML-reported NUMA node has CPUs. If not, fall through to CPU-affinity-based detection which resolves to the nearest CPU-bearing NUMA node.\r\n\r\nHave tested it on non-CDMM GB200 servers.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n<details>\r\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\r\n\r\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\r\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\r\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\r\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\r\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n",
